review_blob: Pours with almost no head. More on the malt (caramel, nutty feel) side but with a nice touch of extra hops in the end which is a bit unusual for this style (but expected considering it s made in USA)

Dark with medium head. Olives and alcohol on the nose. Coffee, roasted apples and nice lingering alcohol in the end. Medium sweetness with a very nicely balanced biterness in the after taste. The body is spectacular, you almost feel like drinking oil. Absolutely amazing beer!

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Pours amber with medium-big head. Medium sweetness, lightly sour with a creamy body and a nicely balanced bitterness in the end. This one is a big surprise. For some reason I avoided it for a long while probably because of the ugly label (how superficial of me!). Now that I tasted it I cannnot stop drinkin. Not a mountain of flavour but damn this is well balanced and subtle, and the worst of all (for my liver) incredibily drinkable. Probably the best trappist Ive ever tried. Im goindown to the supermarket to buy another one, two, three... oh, please stop me!
Dark brown with small head. Nice fruity flavor thats a bit watered down. OK, but couldve been better.
Dark with big head. Sweet, alcohol, dark fruits, winey and creamy. Complex, each sip reveals something new, I even felt something like roses at some point. Very good!
beer_name: De Dochter van de Korenaar Embrasse

review_blob: Pours dark ruby with a big head. Sweet and sour, grapes. You can literally taste the barrel as you drink (in a good way). Excellent sour!

Pours amber with a medium head. Piney, bitter, grassy. Too grassy. I like my pale ale more fruity/citrussy. Also, its flavor goes away with each sip. Correct, but there are far better variants for this style.
Nice hops aroma. Flavour is citrussy and fruity. Medium sweetnes, medium biterness. The aftertaste is great: a subtle piney note that reminds of pinecone buds syrup. Very good!
Romanian version, not sure it s the same as the original. Not much to say: Your usual pale lager, pretty refreshing when cold enough. Slightly better than other shitty lagers.

Creamy head, hoppy aroma. First it hits you with a coffee note then it goes along with a classic citrussy taste. Moderate sweetness, medium biterness. Creamier than Raven from Thornbridge which is good. This is how black ipa should be done. Very good!
beer_name: Green Flash Hop Odyssey Black IPA

review_blob: Quite interesting. Its not really an APA, but more of a pilsener hell APA (it has that grassy and crisp character that you can usually find in pilseners/hells, but with the citrussy twist of a pale ale). Reduced biterness (for this style), medium sweetness. Overall, refreshing and nicely balanced beer, excellent for hot summer days.
Nicely hopped and easy to drink. Excelent for hot summer days. Quite a surprise. It reminded me of Oakham Citra (probably because of the citra hops, doh :D).

Pours hazy light golden. Light sweetness, medium bitterness, medium body. The fruity aromas are very nicely balanced without being too agressive. Very easy to drink which is actually pretty dangerous, since it has a high ABV. An India Pale Ale exactly how I like it.

Pours hazy dark amber with a decent head. Caramel, fruit (strawberry?) jam and spices. Medium sweetness, ligh bitterness. Interestingly similar to dunkel, but with more hops (which is good!). Goes well in colder weather (autumn-winter) but I wont refuse one in summer either. Very nice and tasty!
Medium sweetness, medium to light bitterness, light body, thin feel, average carbonation. Elder and citrus aromas. Light ale, not a masterpiece, but very nice for hot summer days.

Pours amber with a almost no head. Raisin aroma, medium sweetness, high bitterness, medium body, oily feel, very soft carbonation, almost flat. It feels somehow like a very light cognac. Thats nice, since I like cognac, but it isnt something I expect in a beer. My second (very) strong ale (after I Hardcore You) and I realize this is definitely not my style.
beer_name: Flying Dog Double Dog Double Pale Ale

review_blob: Surprisingly good one. Nicely balanced and refreshing. Excellent for hot summer days. Medium sweetness, medium bitterness, light body.
